PRIORITIES
==========
1. Health & Security: We will never support an amendment that could compromise the stability, security, or overall health of the XRP Ledger.
2. Self-Interest: As a development company, we recognize that our decisions may carry bias due to how amendments affect our own tools and projects. 
  We strive for transparency about potential conflicts of interest.
3. Innovation: We are committed to supporting new use cases and features for the XRP Ledger without stifling innovation.
4. Community Demand: We actively seek and engage in community conversations to gather feedback and better understand end-user requirements.

CRITERIA
========
1. Community Input: We strive to maintain an unbiased position by actively engaging in public conversations.
2. Audit Results: We do not conduct our own independent audits. Instead, we assess the quality and credibility of publicly released audit reports.
3. Testing Results: We do not perform our own independent amendment tests. Instead, we assess the quality and credibility of publicly released test
  results.


